      "content": "I hear the deep frustration and despair in your words. It sounds like you're experiencing a profound sense of loss and disconnection, where the vibrant parts of your personality feel like they've vanished, leaving you feeling hollow and like a ghost in your own life. This feeling of emptiness and the exhaustion of pretending to be someone else can be incredibly overwhelming.\n\nWhile I understand that therapy might not feel like a solution to you right now, it's important to remember that these feelings are valid and shared by many people who are struggling with similar experiences. Sometimes, when we feel this way, it can be helpful to talk to someone who can listen without judgment or try to find support in a community that understands these deep emotional struggles.\n\nPlease know that you are not alone in this experience, and there are people who can help you navigate these difficult feelings. If you feel overwhelmed or in crisis, please consider reaching out to a crisis hotline or a mental health professional who can provide support tailored to your needs.",
